 <H1>Architectural Adaptation</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Each of the following elements can benefit from increased adaptability (above and beyond CPU programming)
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>CPU
<LI>Memory hierarchy : eliminate false sharing
<LI>Memory system : virtual memory layout based on cache miss data
<LI>IO : disk layout based on access pattern
<LI>Network interface : scheduling to reduced end-to-end latency
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Adaptability used to build
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>programmable engines in IO, memory controllers, cache controllers, network devices
<LI>configurable data-paths and logic in any part of the system
<LI>configurable queueing in scheduling for interconnect, devices, memory
<LI>smart interfaces for information flow from applications to hardware
<LI>performance monitoring and coordinated resource management...</UL></UL></P>
<P><UL>
Intelligent interfaces, information formats, mechanisms and policies.</UL></P>
<P></P> 
